properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 16 at 5:35PM AKST until February 17 at 12:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blowing snow with visibility around one-half mile
combined with very cold wind chills to around 30 below zero.
Additional snow accumulations of up to one inch. Winds gusting
as high as 40 mph.

* WHERE...The South Klondike Highway north of Skagway.

* WHEN...Until midnight AKST tonight.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions and significant snow
drifts. Areas of blowing snow could significantly reduce
visibility. The cold wind chills as low as 30 below zero could
cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds, snow and blowing snow, and wind
chills will all ease early Monday morning.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling. Bring warm, dry
clothing.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT AKST TONIGHT FOR THE SOUTH KLONDIKE HIGHWAY NEAR WHITE PASS
